"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797640","Department for Education","false","2017-12-04","<p>We expect all local councils to move to paying providers on a monthly basis by September 2018.</p><p>The model agreement, published on 3 March 2017, sets out the department’s expectations and is clear that local councils should pay all providers, particularly childminders, monthly by September 2018. A provider can request to continue an existing alternative and sustainable method of payment as long as the local council agrees.</p><p>In our statutory guidance for early education and childcare we are clear that local councils should use the model agreement unless they have good reason not to do so.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-04T16:35:40.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797640/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797640/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-29","Child Minding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 28 November 2017 to Question 115567 on child minding what proportion of local authorities are paying providers on a monthly basis.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","116603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797641","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-06","<p>The Department undertook a call for evidence on Limited Partnerships into the working of the framework.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is actively considering options for reform and will announce next steps shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-06T13:53:35.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797641/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797641/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-29","Scottish Limited Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has plans to require partners of Scottish Limited Partnerships to provide a correspondence address.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","116604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797642","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-05","<p>Ministers from across Government are speaking with stakeholders from a variety of sectors, to understand their concerns and priorities regarding our exit from the EU. As part of this process, we have engaged with a range of domestic and EU-facing think tanks.</p><p> </p><p>These organisations have contributed to the dialogue around EU withdrawal with a range of insights and opinions on proposed future arrangements, as well as on areas of impact for stakeholders across industry and society.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are publicly available on <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a>.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-12-05T17:29:23.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797642/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797642/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-11-29","Department for Exiting the European Union: Legatum Institute","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what meetings Ministers of his Department have had with representatives of the Legatum Institute in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","116605"
